defs.name: with_scale
defs.docs:
Return a new BigDecimal object equivalent to self, with internal
 scaling set to the number specified.
 If the new_scale is lower than the current value (indicating a larger
 power of 10), digits will be dropped (as precision is lower)

defs.name: with_prec
defs.docs: Return a new BigDecimal object with precision set to new value

defs.name: sign
defs.docs: Return the sign of the `BigDecimal` as `num::bigint::Sign`.

defs.name: as_bigint_and_exponent
defs.docs:
Return the internal big integer value and an exponent. Note that a positive
 exponent indicates a negative power of 10.

defs.name: into_bigint_and_exponent
defs.docs:
Convert into the internal big integer value and an exponent. Note that a positive
 exponent indicates a negative power of 10.

defs.name: digits
defs.docs: Number of digits in the non-scaled integer representation

defs.name: abs
defs.docs: Compute the absolute value of number

defs.name: sqrt
defs.docs: Take the square root of the number

defs.name: cbrt
defs.docs: Take the cube root of the number

defs.name: inverse
defs.docs: Compute the reciprical of the number: x<sup>-1</sup>

defs.name: is_integer
defs.docs:
Return true if this number has zero fractional part (is equal
 to an integer)
